    Risk of adverse pregnancy outcomes prior to the onset of an autoimmune rheumatic disease: a systematic review.
 Our findings of an increased risk of APO in certain preARD highlights the relevance of an obstetric history during the first rheumatology appointment and the need for novel screening strategies to predict APO. Further research is required to elucidate the immune basis of adverse pregnancy outcomes in preclinical and clinical ARD.
